snippet.textDisplay:
So I like to find the things in common with other characteristics of other mvs, and I saw from the start the colors reminding me a lot of Monsta X/early exo vibes (just like the choreo from Overdose in the pre chorus here).
Then the Flags like Bigbang and Ateez, cool.
The lake in the beginning was a lot like Nayeon in Fancy!
And again Monsta X in the hang movements of pre chorus... but also Exo CBX in the chorus for the shoulder move!
The ceiling being so short reminds a lot of BTS in Wings and also Black On Black by NCT.
OHH wow and the crystal line on the face like Baekhyun in Obsession, and the move on the floor like Yeji in Dalla Dalla.
And, last but not least, the cage and hair style similiar to Sunmi in Siren!

Of course I love how they all did it in their own way and nothing is too obvious <3 love their energy and the invasive closeup of some scenes!!
And I LOVE the recurring scene they're having of the being frozen!!

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm so glad everyone in the comments is talking about the line distribution, if we can talk about this this much maybe they will hear us, It's not fair for anyone of the members, Mia is being so overworked, and the other members (specially onda who was meant to have the dance break because she is a lead dancer and a lead vocalist but they only gave her little center time and adlibs) are being mistreated, it's a group, it's not fair to have anyone to only say lalala and the other to only say you're so dun dun dun, the company isn't letting them show their real talent, why not give the dance break to E;U or Onda? Why not give the pre chorus to Silhyeon? Why not give real lines to Yiren or Onda? Why not give more rapping lines to E;U and Aisha? Why not give more screentime and lines to other members? The fact that the fans can imagine a better line distribution than the freaking company really speaks a lot.
The excuse that Yena is going to join everglow isn't an excuse to give Mia a whole minute singing and a lot of center time and a lot of screentime, they can give a fair line distribution and the other things even if Yena is going to join, and Mia being the "ace" or the group isn't an excuse neither, she's a main vocalist and a main dancer, but in adios she even got a rap, E;U is a main dancer too, and Silhyeon is a lead vocalist that deserves being a main vocalist, if Mia is going to get every line and every dance then make her a soloist, the company is overworking her and this is not right for her or for other members, the distributions really matter a lot, they're idols they come here to get the right management, the distributions help the members to get popularity and being remembered, for example, why y'all think Onda is so underrated? Because they don't even let her shine, and I'm sure Mia is going to get hurt by all of this, all the overwork they are giving her, give her a break and give the other members an opportunity to shine, i really hope that everglow next comeback will have a better distribution, this song is a bop but this just isn't fair
